==German==
===Etymology===
Compound of ''[[hoch]]'' and ''[[Zeit]]'', originally meaning "high celebration"
===Pronunciation===
# "marriage": with an open ''o''.
# "heyday": with a longer, more closed ''o''.
===Noun===
'''Hochzeit''' ''f'' (''pl'' Hochzeiten)

# [[marriage]], [[wedding]]
# [[heyday]], [[height]]

===Usage===
* ''Es war die '''Hochzeit''' der Azteken.'' - It was the heyday of the Aztecs.

